Reasoning: The paper deals with the application of deep learning for the diagnosis of a skin disease. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of autoencoders and deep neural networks also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as word embeddings, which falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the use of traditional machine learning methods such as Extreme Gradient Boosting suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE).
